-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Industrias Romi, Petrobras, Tecnisa
-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 2011-12-23T13:22:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/brazilian-stock-movers-industrias-romi-petrobras-tecnisa.html
The following companies are having
 unusual (IBOV)  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:13 a.m. local time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa index rose 0.6 percent to 57,688.46.  Industrias Romi SA  (ROMI3 BS) gained 4.5 percent to 6
reais. The Brazilian machinery manufacturer paid 20.5 million
euros ($26.8 million) for Burkhardt + Weber Fertigungssysteme
GmbH, a German manufacturer of  machine tools , according to a
regulatory filing.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS) rose 0.8 percent to 22.33
reais as crude futures climbed 0.3 percent in  New York .  Brazil ’s
state-controlled oil company found traces of oil and natural gas
in two onshore wells in the country’s Solimoes Basin, according
to a posting on the website of the National Petroleum Agency.
The discoveries haven’t yet been declared commercially viable.  Tecnisa SA  (TCSA3 BS) rose 4.2 percent to 10.43 reais. The
Brazilian real-estate firm said it sold a 6.35 percent stake in
Windsor Investimentos Imobiliarios Ltda. to BV Empreendimentos &
Participacoes SA for 50 million reais ($27 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
